overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their recently
  implemented sleep questionnaire application, including its database and API
  endpoints, against a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The agent
  performed an in-depth analysis, identifying several critical gaps and missing
  features such as a tiredness severity scale with safety warnings, explicit
  detection for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient
  Sleep Syndrome, and the inclusion of outbound resource links in the generated
  reports. Following this review, the agent proceeded to implement these
  high-priority items. This involved updating data types, validation schemas,
  modifying the questionnaire UI to include the severity scale, and enhancing
  both the web-based and PDF reports to incorporate the new diagnostic logic and
  resource links. The implementation ensures the questionnaire now provides more
  nuanced assessments and actionable guidance to users.
